reviewText: Quigley Down Under is one of my husband and my favorite movies. We had an old VHS version of it, but it's become stretched.  I was glad to find this CD for a good price. For anyone unfamiliar with the movie's general plot,  I'd recommend the Internet Movie Data Base site (imdb) for a general idea.  The CD was in good condition - packaged to protect the merchandise and in a normal plastic case.  I haven't watched Rob Roy yet.  I imagine we will soon.

reviewText: Drama and action, all rolled up into one neat, little package. This 2 pack is a really good deal. Both films are the get even sort, as far as story lines go, and both showcase some beautiful nature scenery. Big name actors and actresses play in both the films. If you're a fan of action/adventure, or films where the underdog comes out on top, then I'd highly recommend these 2.
